# Agent Workflow

## Before editing

1. Read the project's `AGENTS.md` (if present) for repo map, stack, and deploy context.
2. Check relevant `.agents/rules/*.mdc` for files you will touch.
3. Invoke a skill for multi-step tasks (bootstrap, deploy, feature workflows).

## Scope

- One concern per change; minimize diff size.
- Do not scaffold app features during rules-only or docs-only tasks.
- Match existing code style and abstractions in the target repo.

## Shared skills

If the project uses [agent-utils](https://github.com/your-org/agent-utils) skills, copy or reference them from `.agents/skills/`. Project-specific skill names and triggers belong in the app's `AGENTS.md`.

## Git

Commit or open PRs **only when the user asks**.
